@startuml
title Viaverse Quote / Offer — Class Model

class Quote {
  id: QuoteId
  requestId: RequestId
  senderType: WORKER | BUSINESS
  workerProfileId: UUID?
  businessId: UUID?
  status: QuoteStatus
  price: Money
  message: String
  estimatedStart: Instant?
  estimatedDuration: Duration?
  expiresAt: Instant
  createdAt: Instant
}

class QuoteRevision {
  id: UUID
  quoteId: QuoteId
  price: Money?
  message: String?
  reason: String?
  createdBy: AccountId
  createdAt: Instant
}

class QuotePolicy {
  canSendQuote()
  canReviseQuote()
  canWithdrawQuote()
  canAcceptQuote()
  validateQuoteNotExpired()
  validateRequestOwner()
}

class ServiceRequest {
  id: RequestId
  requesterAccountId: AccountId
  status: RequestStatus
  budget: Budget
  categoryId: CategoryId
}

class Job {
  id: JobId
  requestId: RequestId
  acceptedQuoteId: QuoteId
  status: JobStatus
  createdAt: Instant
}

class QuoteEvents {
  QuoteSent
  QuoteRevised
  QuoteWithdrawn
  QuoteRejected
  QuoteAccepted
  JobCreated
}

class OutboxEvent {
  id: UUID
  aggregateType
  aggregateId
  eventType
  payload
  correlationId
  causationId
}

class QuoteVisibilityRule {
  requester can view all own quotes
  sender can view own quote
  competitors cannot view each other
  admin requires audit
}

Quote "1" o-- "*" QuoteRevision
Quote --> ServiceRequest : belongs to
QuotePolicy ..> Quote : validates
QuotePolicy ..> ServiceRequest : checks owner/state
Quote --> Job : accepted creates
Quote ..> QuoteEvents : emits
QuoteEvents --> OutboxEvent : serialized as
QuoteVisibilityRule ..> Quote : protects

note bottom
Quote acceptance must be atomic:
one accepted quote per request,
competing quotes transition out of selectable state,
and Job draft is created.
end note
@enduml
